THERESA GOH: You
should have changed

00:42:12.190 --> 00:42:14.836
AUDIENCE: It was one
hour ago or something.

00:42:14.836 --> 00:42:16.210
So I actually have
two questions,

00:42:16.210 --> 00:42:18.350
but I suppose there's
only time for one.

00:42:18.350 --> 00:42:20.176
One actually relates
to disabilities,

00:42:20.176 --> 00:42:22.300
and the other one is actually
Singapore in general.

00:42:22.300 --> 00:42:26.290
So the first one was around--

00:42:26.290 --> 00:42:30.640
and you don't have to answer
this if it's sensitive.

00:42:30.640 --> 00:42:33.820
But during the Paralympics,
Olympics, or [INAUDIBLE],

00:42:33.820 --> 00:42:36.040
rather, there was a lot of
celebrations in Singapore,

00:42:36.040 --> 00:42:40.330
and also a lot of chatter and
talk about the monetary reward,

00:42:40.330 --> 00:42:41.946
and the discrepancies--

00:42:41.946 --> 00:42:44.320
I'm not sure this was already
covered-- but discrepancies

00:42:44.320 --> 00:42:47.590
between both, and just wanted
to get some of your thoughts

00:42:47.590 --> 00:42:49.694
on how you feel about that.

00:42:49.694 --> 00:42:51.610
I think you were quoted
in the papers as well.

00:42:51.610 --> 00:42:54.110
But it would be great to hear
some of your personal thoughts

00:42:54.110 --> 00:42:56.290
and reflections on
the discrepancies

00:42:56.290 --> 00:42:57.520
and how that affects--

00:42:57.520 --> 00:43:00.100
or whether you
think that's fair,

00:43:00.100 --> 00:43:03.520
what you would like to
see changing going forward

00:43:03.520 --> 00:43:05.510
in Singapore, and the
perception of Olympians

00:43:05.510 --> 00:43:07.240
versus Paralympians.

00:43:07.240 --> 00:43:09.440
And then the second thing was--

00:43:09.440 --> 00:43:12.100
it's very stark or
very interesting

00:43:12.100 --> 00:43:16.060
that swimming seems to be
the sport in Singapore that

00:43:16.060 --> 00:43:20.530
earns us medals, both
for able-bodied athletes

00:43:20.530 --> 00:43:21.490
and Paralympians.

00:43:21.490 --> 00:43:23.980
And just wanted to
get your view on how

00:43:23.980 --> 00:43:26.770
we can replicate the success
for other sports in Singapore

00:43:26.770 --> 00:43:29.150
as well.

00:43:29.150 --> 00:43:31.880
THERESA GOH: I'm going to
touch the first question first.

00:43:31.880 --> 00:43:36.620
The easiest way to say is
if you were a Paralympian,

00:43:36.620 --> 00:43:41.360
and you had gotten a gold
medal, and your friend is

00:43:41.360 --> 00:43:44.150
an Olympian got a gold
medal, and both of you

00:43:44.150 --> 00:43:46.070
have gone through the
same kind of trainings,

00:43:46.070 --> 00:43:47.695
and basically got
into the same things,

00:43:47.695 --> 00:43:51.190
how will you feel if you've
got different amounts?

00:43:51.190 --> 00:43:57.410
So that's the way that it allows
you to feel, how we would feel.

00:43:57.410 --> 00:43:59.720
But at the same time,
it's also not something

00:43:59.720 --> 00:44:04.290
that we worry about because it's
not something we can control.

00:44:04.290 --> 00:44:08.680
And I think in
life, my whole life,

00:44:08.680 --> 00:44:11.720
it's always not worrying about
something you cannot control.

00:44:11.720 --> 00:44:13.890
So you control what
you can control.

00:44:13.890 --> 00:44:16.340
And if you control something,
you cannot control it,

00:44:16.340 --> 00:44:19.260
it just makes you
more frustrated.

00:44:19.260 --> 00:44:21.650
So I think it's also a lot--

00:44:21.650 --> 00:44:25.340
we like to compare it to--

00:44:25.340 --> 00:44:27.650
because Paralympic sports
is not so competitive--

00:44:27.650 --> 00:44:32.150
so I think one of the
[INAUDIBLE] something.

00:44:32.150 --> 00:44:33.800
And that's not really
a fair comparison

00:44:33.800 --> 00:44:36.133
because there are different
sports with different levels

00:44:36.133 --> 00:44:38.120
of competitive level--
not competitive level,

00:44:38.120 --> 00:44:41.200
different levels of
numbers of competition.

00:44:41.200 --> 00:44:43.970
And swimming has a lot of
competitors, a lot of swimmers.

00:44:43.970 --> 00:44:47.690
But then if you compare another
sport, maybe it has two-thirds.

00:44:47.690 --> 00:44:49.890
Are you giving that sport
lesser even though it's

00:44:49.890 --> 00:44:50.970
an able-bodied sport?

00:44:50.970 --> 00:44:51.900
All right.

00:44:51.900 --> 00:44:55.280
So I think that's not really
a fair comparison to make.

00:44:55.280 --> 00:44:57.170
The main point is
that they probably

00:44:57.170 --> 00:45:03.560
don't value personal
disability s highly

00:45:03.560 --> 00:45:05.300
as an able-bodied person.

00:45:05.300 --> 00:45:07.070
That's how I feel like.

00:45:07.070 --> 00:45:09.980
I feel that's the main
base, the foundation of it.

00:45:09.980 --> 00:45:12.720
That is why they feel that
we don't deserve as much,

00:45:12.720 --> 00:45:13.760
even though they don't--

00:45:13.760 --> 00:45:17.312
they may not realize that
they're feeling that way.

00:45:17.312 --> 00:45:18.770
YIP PIN XIU: And
they don't realize

00:45:18.770 --> 00:45:21.890
that not many people get their
knowledge or their information

00:45:21.890 --> 00:45:23.840
from papers or from things.

00:45:23.840 --> 00:45:27.290
So if the people at the top--

00:45:27.290 --> 00:45:32.720
not exactly the top-- but if
people don't see us as equals,

00:45:32.720 --> 00:45:34.389
then people read
the news, and they

00:45:34.389 --> 00:45:36.180
see that they're not
equal, they would also

00:45:36.180 --> 00:45:38.513
start to have this mindset
that-- oh, maybe they are not

00:45:38.513 --> 00:45:42.470
equal, which is a bit painful.

00:45:42.470 --> 00:45:45.055
But I think we
don't take the money

00:45:45.055 --> 00:45:46.930
thing too hard because
we're really not doing

00:45:46.930 --> 00:45:48.600
this for the money.

00:45:48.600 --> 00:45:49.124
Yeah.

00:45:49.124 --> 00:45:51.540
So maybe you don't have to
increase our amount but maybe--

00:45:51.540 --> 00:45:53.750
THERESA GOH: Bring
down the Olympians'.

00:45:53.750 --> 00:45:57.090
YIP PIN XIU: I didn't say that.

00:45:57.090 --> 00:45:58.090
Yeah.

